      "stem_html": "<p>Rank the following compounds in order of increasing acidity:</p>\n<p><b>(a)</b><img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaUVZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--10fc3f7edc7583d212d8603ac7dadd6f40a45c4d/OChem_22_EC_030a.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of propanoic acid.\">\n <b>(b)</b><img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaUlZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--96125c0821b0c645c3a293ea2191defb823b3249/OChem_22_EC_030b.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of ethanol\">\n <b>(c)</b><img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaU1ZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--2f205aa1497c812fa1576df2aaf18700fec15d59/OChem_22_EC_030c.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of diethyl amine where the N H group is bonded to two ethyl groups.\">\n <b>(d)</b><img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaVFZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--341bbae5bb083a5d3407ddd0e5d3868ac65b8ac3/OChem_22_EC_030d.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of acetone where a central carbonyl group is bonded to two methyl groups.\">\n <b>(e)</b><img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaVVZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--e00122b1ccf91428e1b1281674f68aaff66a0a63/OChem_22_EC_030e.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of pentane-2,4-dione, carbonyl groups being at C 2 and C 4 of a five carbon chain.\">\n <b>(f)</b><img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaVlZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--df98872c399536d90b83a8128edd1d75149c8afe/OChem_22_EC_030f.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of trichloroacetic acid where a trichloromethyl group is attached to a carboxylic acid group.\"></p>",
